President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key positions in his administration. These include Carol Z. Perez as Director General of the Foreign Service at the Department of State. Perez is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and has served as the Ambassador to the Republic of Chile since 2016. Joel Szabat is nominated as Assistant Secretary for Aviation and International Affairs at the Department of Transportation. He currently serves as the Deputy Assistant Secretary for the Office of Aviation and International Affairs. Kelvin Droegemeier is nominated as Director of the Office of Science and Technology Policy. He currently serves as Vice President for Research and Regents' Professor of Meteorology at the University of Oklahoma. Lastly, Robert Ord is appointed as a Member of the American Battle Monuments Commission.